# Code quality

- Do not generate excessive comments.
- Comments must explain intent or non-obvious business rules only.
- Avoid duplicate structures or repeated conditional logic.
- Remove unreachable code and dead branches.
- Prefer refactoring over patching around old code.
- Call out unused imports, vars, and functions.
- If you detect duplicate logic, unreachable code, or dead code in existing files, point it out and suggest a refactor.
